POP:Procedural Oriented Programming

OOP:Object Oriented Programming

Features of OOP
1)object:Any Entity which has own state and behaviour
ex:pen,paper,chair etc..

2)class:collection of objects that is called class
ex:human body

3)abstraction:hiding internal details and show functionalities
ex:facebook login page

4)encapsulation:Wrapping up of data or binding of data
ex:capsule

5)inheritance:when one object acquire all the properties and behaviour of 
parent class
ex:remote and phone

6)polymorphism:Many ways to perform anything
ex:road ways
Types of polymorphism
1)Method Overloading
2)Methof Overriding


Constructor:Method having a same as a classname that is called a constructor

types of constructor
1)Default ->There is a no parameter
2)Parameterized ->there is some parameter(arguments)

=>this is refrence keyword
=>static keyword
1)variable->Use same memory for reallocation
2)method
3)block

